      • updateRule

        @ColumnLabel(value="UPDATE_RULE")
private short updateRule
        What happens to foreign key when primary is updated:.
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyNoAction - do not allow update of primary key if it has been imported
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyCascade - change imported key to agree with primary key update
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeySetNull - change imported key to NULL if its primary key has been updated
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeySetDefault - change imported key to default values if its primary key has been updated
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyRestrict - same as importedKeyNoAction (for ODBC 2.x compatibility)

      • deleteRule

        @ColumnLabel(value="DELETE_RULE")
private short deleteRule
        What happens to the foreign key when primary is deleted.
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyNoAction - do not allow delete of primary key if it has been imported
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyCascade - delete rows that import a deleted key
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeySetNull - change imported key to NULL if its primary key has been deleted
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyRestrict - same as importedKeyNoAction (for ODBC 2.x compatibility)
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeySetDefault - change imported key to default if its primary key has been deleted

      • fkName

      • deferrability

        @ColumnLabel(value="DEFERRABILITY")
private short deferrability
        can the evaluation of foreign key constraints be deferred until commit.
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyInitiallyDeferred - see SQL92 for definition
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyInitiallyImmediate - see SQL92 for definition
        • DatabaseMetaData.importedKeyNotDeferrable - see SQL92 for definition
